---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="TELOS | Problems Missions Goals and Life Direction" description="Personal framework for tracking purpose and direction in life">
  <main class="relative z-10 pt-28 pb-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h1 class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl text-gradient mb-4">TELOS Framework</h1>
        <p class="font-body text-lg text-text-secondary">
          A structured approach to understanding problems, defining missions, setting goals, and measuring progress.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Problems -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-accent bg-accent/20 px-3 py-1 rounded">P</span>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-text-primary">Problems</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="font-body text-text-secondary mb-6">
          The most important issues I see that need solving.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="bg-bg-secondary rounded-xl border border-border-default p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-accent shrink-0">P1</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-heading text-lg text-text-primary mb-2">Technical teams struggle to adopt AI safely without proper guardrails</h3>
                <p class="font-body text-sm text-text-secondary">
                  Organizations need frameworks to implement AI securely while maintaining data privacy and operational safety.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-bg-secondary rounded-xl border border-border-default p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-accent shrink-0">P2</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-heading text-lg text-text-primary mb-2">ADHD makes traditional productivity systems fail; we need different approaches</h3>
                <p class="font-body text-sm text-text-secondary">
                  Standard task management and workflow systems don't account for ADHD executive function challenges.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-bg-secondary rounded-xl border border-border-default p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-accent shrink-0">P3</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-heading text-lg text-text-primary mb-2">Infrastructure knowledge is siloed; patterns should be shared openly</h3>
                <p class="font-body text-sm text-text-secondary">
                  Enterprise-grade infrastructure patterns are locked behind corporate walls instead of shared for community benefit.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Missions -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-brand bg-brand/20 px-3 py-1 rounded">M</span>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-text-primary">Missions</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="font-body text-text-secondary mb-6">
          My approaches to addressing these problems.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="bg-bg-secondary rounded-xl border border-border-default p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-brand shrink-0">M1</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-heading text-lg text-text-primary mb-2">Provide security-first AI consulting through GoodFields</h3>
                <p class="font-body text-sm text-text-secondary">
                  Help technical teams adopt AI safely with proper security frameworks and operational guardrails.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-bg-secondary rounded-xl border border-border-default p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-brand shrink-0">M2</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-heading text-lg text-text-primary mb-2">Build and share ADHD-optimized AI workflows through Bob/PAI</h3>
                <p class="font-body text-sm text-text-secondary">
                  Create AI assistant frameworks that work with ADHD executive function rather than against it.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-bg-secondary rounded-xl border border-border-default p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-brand shrink-0">M3</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-heading text-lg text-text-primary mb-2">Document enterprise patterns at home-lab scale through FabLab</h3>
                <p class="font-body text-sm text-text-secondary">
                  Share production-grade infrastructure patterns in accessible, reproducible formats.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Goals -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-success bg-success/20 px-3 py-1 rounded">G</span>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-text-primary">Goals</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="font-body text-text-secondary mb-6">
          Specific goals are tracked in Vikunja and managed by Bob/PAI for ADHD-optimized task flow.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-bg-secondary rounded-xl border border-border-default p-6">
          <p class="font-body text-sm text-text-secondary">
            Rather than defining static long-term goals here, I use an ADHD-friendly approach:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 font-body text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <li>• <strong>Daily compass checks</strong> to align actions with mission</li>
            <li>• <strong>Build blocks</strong> (60-120 min focused work) tracked in Vikunja</li>
            <li>• <strong>Bob's gentle accountability</strong> for task flow and handoffs</li>
            <li>• <strong>Ship-and-iterate</strong> over rigid planning</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Footer -->
      <section class="border-t border-border-subtle pt-8">
        <p class="font-body text-sm text-text-tertiary italic">
          TELOS is my framework for purpose and direction. It's not about rigid planning—it's about knowing <em>why</em> so the <em>what</em> becomes clearer. The problems define the terrain. The missions chart the path. The goals emerge from daily action.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
